\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\ql\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 Yet apart from an argument based on a hard conflict, which might be recognised as a gesture to comity, even on the {\ul\ulc0 Hartford Fire}{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s14\cf0\qj\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\ul\ulc0  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang1033\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033 Hartford Fire Insurance Company v California 509 US 764 (1993).}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang1033\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033  }{\cf1\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang1033\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033 We deal with this case below.}}}}
 approach, no other legal principle for such a distinction was advanced, nor any economic one.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s14\cf0\qj\rtlch\af6\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs20\lang1033\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 The respondents initially advanced the proposition that the United States had provided for Webb-Pomerene associations in order to further their foreign trade interests and that comity required us to acknowledge this in our treatment of Ansac. This argumen
