. Indeed on the contrary both constitutional values and the common law rules of statutory interpretation require us not to interpret a statute even if ambiguous in a manner that would lead to an unreasonable result.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\ql\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 In the present case it is not disputed that we are dealing with customary international law and not an international agreement. How then do we know when a rule is to be regarded as customary international law in the Republic?}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\ql\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 
