ition. Black\'92s Law Dictionary in defining \'91comity\'92 quotes an extract from the literature where the authors complain that:}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\cf1 \'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\cf1\ltrch\hich\f4\lang2057\loch\f4\lang2057 A great deal of misconception about the nature of conflict of laws is due to the loose use of the term \'91comity\'92.\'94}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch {\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f4\lang2057\loch\f4\lang2057 See Black\'92s Law Dictionary, quoting H.Goodrich and E Scoles }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang2057\i\loch\f6\fs20\lang2057\i Handbook of the Conflict of laws}{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang2057\loch\f6\fs20\lang2057 . Black\'92s also quotes Macalister- Smith who says the term is misleadingly used as a synonym for international law.}{\cf6\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang2057\loch\f6\fs20\lang2057  }{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\lang2057\loch\f6\fs20\lang2057 According to Griffin the European Commission bel
ieves that comity is a matter for prosecutorial discretion rather than a legal prerequisite for jurisdiction. See Griffin op cit, page 77 footnote 88.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\ql\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang2057\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20 In }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20 Laker Airways Ltd v Sabena, Belgian World Airlines, 731 F.2d 909 (D.C. Cir. 1984)}{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20 , comity is described as the }{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\i\loch\f6\fs20\i \'93 degree of deference that a domestic forum must pay to the act of a foreign government not otherwise binding on the forum\'94}{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20  The }{\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20 Laker}{\ltrch\hich\f6\fs20\loch\f6\fs20  decision 
